-- Alstom Close to Non-Reactor Venture with BHEL, Nuclear Power, Line Reports
-- Madelene Pearson
-- 2010-06-25T01:35:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/alstom-close-to-non-reactor-venture-with-bhel-nuclear-power-line-reports.html

          
          
             Alstom S.A., the turbine supplier to
a third of the nuclear stations worldwide, is close to
finalizing talks for a tripartite venture with state-owned
Nuclear Power Corp of India Ltd. and Bharat Heavy Electricals
Ltd., the Hindu Business Line newspaper reported, citing Alstom
Power Senior Vice-President for Thermal Products Guy Chardon.  
 The venture is for executing the non-reactor part of
upcoming nuclear projects, the newspaper said. Alstom expects to
have a 33 percent stake in the proposed three-way venture, it
said.  
